OL,6,FNatasha Clark, Senior Crown Prosecutor
OL,7,Ffor Crown Prosecution Service North
OL,8,FWest, said the former Blackburn Rovers
OL,9,Fplayer's behaviour was "intimidating
OL,10,Fand persistent", stating he "ignored
OL,11,Fher wishes and breached boundaries she
OL,12,Fput in place, using multiple different
OL,13,Fplatforms to contact her."
OL,15,FShe added: "Hendry's behaviour was
OL,16,Fintimidating and persistent, causing
OL,17,Fthe victim immense distress, but
OL,18,Fdespite this he initially refused to
OL,19,Faccept it was harassment.
